'''Overfinch''' is a company that customises [[Land Rovers]] and [[Range Rover]]s and is based in [[Leeds]], [[England]]. In 2005, Overfinch won the Ford "Special Recognition for Outstanding Achievement in Design" award for the SuperSport styling package.<ref>{{Cite news |title=In tune with Ireland's needs |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/newspaper/motors/2008/0806/1217923970362.html |last=O'Donoghue |first=Shane |newspaper=[[The Irish Times]] |date=8 August 2008 | accessdate=3 August 2010}}</ref> In November 2010, Overfinch was placed into administration, under the control of administrators Wilson Field, who claimed the business had incurred significant one-off non-trading costs which hit cash flow.<ref>{{Cite magazine |title=Range Rover tuner Overfinch goes bust |url=http://www.autoexpress.co.uk/land-rover/range-rover/34401/range-rover-tuner-overfinch-goes-bust | magazine=[[Auto Express]] |date=16 November 2010 |accessdate=25 November 2010}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Overfinch In Administration |url=http://www.pistonheads.com/news/default.asp?storyId=22778 |website=Pistonheads |date=16 November 2010 | accessdate=16 November 2010}}</ref> Autobrokers Ltd of Leeds (who had traded for the previous four years as the Overfinch Vehicle Retailing Division under then name 'Overfinch Leeds'), acquired the business and assets.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.motortrader.com/motor-trader-news/automotive-news/overfinch-bought-out-of-administration-17-12-2010 |title=Overfinch bought out of administration |first=Curtis |last=Hutchinson |date=17 December 2010 |magazine=Motor Trader |accessdate=14 February 2011}}</ref> Models include the Overfinch 580 S,<ref>{{Cite magazine |title=Overfinch Range Rover 580S |url=http://www.evo.co.uk/carreviews/evocarreviews/33941/range_rover.html |last=Metcalfe |first=Harry |magazine=[[Evo (magazine)|Evo]] |date=February 2003 |accessdate=3 August 2010 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080127091133/http://www.evo.co.uk/carreviews/evocarreviews/33941/range_rover.html |archive-date=27 January 2008}}</ref> the 2010 Overfinch Vogue GT (based on Range Rover), Overfinch SuperSport (based on Range Rover Sport),<ref>{{Cite magazine |title=First drives, Range Rover Overfinch SuperSport |url=http://www.autocar.co.uk/CarReviews/FirstDrives/Land-Rover-Range-Rover-4.2-V8-Overfinch-Supersport/221954/ |last=Quirk |first=Jon |magazine=[[Autocar (magazine)|Autocar]] |date=21 August 2006 |accessdate=3 August 2010 }}</ref> and [[Holland & Holland]] Overfinch.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Holland and Holland Overfinch Range Rover: the most luxurious model yet |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/motoring/news/6240416/Holland-and-Holland-Overfinch-Range-Rover-the-most-luxurious-model-yet.html | last=Williams |first=David |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=29 September 2009 |accessdate=2 August 2010}}</ref>
